  "prompt": "I think about a girl constantly. I will never have her and it's unhealthy, how do I stop this?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help move on:\n\n1. Acknowledge your feelings\n\u2022 Accept that your emotions are valid\n\u2022 Recognize this is painful but temporary\n\n2. Create distance\n\u2022 Minimize contact/social media interactions\n\u2022 Avoid places/situations where you might see her\n\n3. Focus on self-improvement\n\u2022 Exercise\n\u2022 Pursue hobbies\n\u2022 Set personal goals\n\u2022 Build self-confidence\n\n4. Process your emotions\n\u2022 Talk to friends\n\u2022 Consider therapy/counseling\n\u2022 Journal your thoughts\n\u2022 Practice mindfulness/meditation\n\n5. Redirect your energy\n\u2022 Meet new people\n\u2022 Try dating when you're ready\n\u2022 Explore new interests\n\u2022 Spend time with friends/family\n\n6. Practice self-compassion\n\u2022 Don't blame yourself\n\u2022 Understand unrequited feelings are normal\n\u2022 Be patient with your healing process\n\n7. Professional help\n\u2022 If obsessive thoughts persist\n\u2022 If you're experiencing depression\n\u2022 If you're struggling to move forward\n\nRemember: Time and active effort will help you heal and move past these intense feelings.\n\nWould you like to discuss any of these strategies in more detail?",
